-- Iraq Arrrests Three Suspected Al-Qaeda Leaders, Agence France-Presse Says
-- Jonathan Burgos
-- 2010-07-25T08:01:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/iraq-arrrests-three-suspected-al-qaeda-leaders-agence-france-presse-says.html

          
          
             Iraqi military arrested three
suspected senior leaders of an al-Qaeda front group in the
country, Agence France-Presse reported, citing a defence
ministry spokeman.  
 Among those arrested was Saleem Khalid al-Zawbayi, the
minister of defence for the Islamic State of Iraq, defence
ministry spokesman Major General Mohammend al-Askari was quoted
by AFP as saying.  
 Zawbayi is suspected of organizing a July 18 suicide
bombing in the town of Radwaniyah, west of Baghdad, that killed
45 people and wounded 46. He was arrested south of the capital.  
 Askari also said two brothers, Jaabar and Qadoori Radhi
Khamis al-Zaidi, believed to have been responsible for
major attacks in the central Iraqi province of Diyala, were
arrested in the northern city of Tikrit.  
